             <lg> 
               <l>The towels rot and disgust me on this damp</l>
               <l>peninsula where they invented mist</l> 
               <l>and drug abuse and taught the light to fade,</l>
               <l>where my top-quality and rock-bottom heart</l>
               <l>cried because I'll never get to kiss</l>
               <l>your famous knees again in a room made</l>
               <l>vague by throwing a scarf over a lamp.</l>
               <l>Things get pretty radical in the dark:</l>
               <l>the sailboats on the inlet sail away;</l>
               <l>the provinces of actuality</l>
               <l>crawl on the sea; the dusk now tenderly</l>
               <l>ministers to the fallen parking lotsâ€”</l>
               <l>the sunset instananeous on the fenders,</l>
               <l>memory and peace . . . the grip of chaos . . .</l>
                 
